l with spatula then churn again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Pour into tin, on top of frozen berry layer.","Place remaining frozen vanilla ice cream squares in mixing bowl and churn <b>40 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and churn again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Pour into tin, level the surface, then freeze for at least 2 hours. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl.","After 2 hours, remove chocolate ice cream from freezer, tip out and cut into squares (3 cm). Place half the frozen squares in mixing bowl and churn <b>40 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then churn again <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b>. Pour into tin, on top of frozen vanilla layer.","Place remaining frozen chocolate ice cream squares in mixing bowl and churn <b>40 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then churn again <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b>. Pour into tin, level the surface, then freeze for at least 8 hours or overnight."]},{"title":"Serving","content":["When ready to serve, remove from tin and invert onto a serving plate, revealing berry ice cream as the top layer. Garnish with berries and a dusting of reserved icing sugar then serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Berry Layer","content":["160 g sugar","500 g double cream","2 egg yolks, from medium eggs","1 tsp vanilla extract","1 pinch fine sea salt","50 g fresh raspberries","150 g blackberries"]},{"title":"Vanilla Layer","content":["470 g double cream","240 g milk","140 g sugar","2 medium eggs","1 ½ tsp vanilla bean paste","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Chocolate Layer","content":["180 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa solids), small pieces or callets","200 g milk","400 g double cream","160 g sugar","4 Tbsp cocoa powder, sifted","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","4 egg yolks, from medium eggs","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Serving","content":["150 g fresh mixed berries"]}],"id":"r95627","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-aLY4qP4YXqo\/XZanbslEJVI\/AAAAAAAAg-8\/D9jXXIO68s0t